      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T03:44:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e \u003e As part of this, are you able to drop pid_t from compat/win/sys/types.h?\n\u003e \u003e Actually, are you able to drop that file altogether?\n\u003e \n\u003e We can drop pid_t. I don\u0027t think we should drop the file altogether, given\n\u003e that it\u0027s injecting \u003cstdint.h\u003e, unless we want to clean that up with an\n\u003e include-what-you-use pass in a separate change.\n\n\u003cstdint.h\u003e is here for historical reasons that no longer apply.\n\nIt was introduced in https://chromium.googlesource.com/crashpad/crashpad/+/07fcf63c2183%5E%21/#F1 to make a former definition of ssize_t and a different (and temporary) definition of pid_t work. pid_t was changed back to “unsigned int” in https://chromium.googlesource.com/crashpad/crashpad/+/ff52791faf30%5E%21/#F1, and ssize_t disappeared entirely in https://chromium.googlesource.com/crashpad/crashpad/+/3d598cdbcd74%5E%21/#F0.\n\n(A further historical note you may find interesting in light of https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/1565288: we did have “unsigned long” here originally, https://chromium.googlesource.com/crashpad/crashpad/+/429a3368d476%5E%21/#F3.)\n\nI don’t think we get any benefit from having a custom \u003csys/types.h\u003e that does its own #include of \u003cstdint.h\u003e on Windows, so I think we should do the follow-up that removes this entirely and adds #includes elsewhere that need to be added as a result, if any.",
      "revId": "c97ac478e70a885d26b2f8a6e1ae9df71c4b6d68",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
